<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3587] Eliminate use of ReadWriteLock in RegionObserver coprocessor invocation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3587</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Follow-up to a discussion on the dev list: &lt;a href=&quot;http://search-hadoop.com/m/jOovV1uAJBP&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://search-hadoop.com/m/jOovV1uAJBP&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The CoprocessorHost ReentrantReadWriteLock is imposing some overhead on data read/write operations, even when no coprocessors are loaded.  Currently execution of RegionCoprocessorHost pre/postXXX() methods are guarded by acquiring the coprocessor read lock.  This is used to prevent coprocessor registration from modifying the coprocessor collection while upcall hooks are in progress.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On further discussion, and looking at the locking in HRegion, it should be sufficient to just use a CopyOnWriteArrayList for the coprocessor collection.  We can then remove the coprocessor lock and eliminate the associated overhead without having to special case the &quot;no loaded coprocessors&quot; condition.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
